Filling:60ml ( cup) jerepigo (or tawny port or hanepoot)100g ( cup) treacle sugar5ml (1 tsp) cinnamon5ml (1 tsp) ground ginger2.5ml ( tsp) ground cloves300g dried apricots, chopped75g sultanas75g raisins30g dried grapesZest and juice of 1 naartjie25ml brandy5ml (1 tsp) vanilla paste60ml ( cup) apricot jamRich Christmas fruit cakeShortcrust pastry:250g flour125g butter, chopped and slightly softened75g vegetable shortening, chopped and slightly softened100g icing sugar, siftedPinch of salt2 egg yolksHertzog topping:60g caster sugar2.5ml ( tsp) baking powder2 egg whites60g desiccated coconutMethod:1) For the filling, place the jerepigo, sugar, spices, dried fruit, naartjie juice and zest in a saucepan over low heat. Simmer gently for 30 minutes, adding a little water if the mixture becomes too dry.2) Once the fruit has broken down, remove pan from heat and stir in the brandy, vanilla and jam. Allow to cool and use as required.3) For the pastry, beat the flour, butter, shortening, icing sugar and salt in a food processor to combine. Add the egg yolks and mix until smooth and well incorporated. Roll dough into a ball, wrap in clingfilm and refrigerate for 30 minutes.4) Roll out the dough on a floured surface and cut into circles large enough to line mini mince pie cases. Refrigerate pastry cases for 15 minutes.5) Preheat the oven to 200 C.6) For the topping, mix the caster sugar and baking powder together. Whisk the egg whites to soft peaks. Fold in the sugar mixture and then the coconut. Transfer to a piping tube.7) Spoon a teaspoon of filling into each pastry case. Pipe the Hertzog topping over the top and bake for 10-15 minutes until golden brown.